I've an unusual background:
- leading software engineer in test at GEO in Cambridge;
- advanced python user;
- experience developing and writing user-level automated tests in a difficult business and technical environment;
- originally trained as a lawyer.

I've been using Robot exclusively for more than a year, leading the testing effort of an embedded connected device that will be installed in millions of homes within the UK. I have recently become a property-based-testing convert, and am one of the first people I know of, who has combined the best property based testing library - Hypothesis - with Robot Framework to produce better user-level verification tests.
